section.section:
In the event of a negotiated sale, the Maryland College Savings Bond Advisory Board shall advise the Board of Public Works regarding:
Public relations and advertising needs;
Bond issuance information, including:
The increments in which to market the bonds;
The recommended maturity dates of the bonds;
The dollar limit that may be imposed on individual household purchases of college savings bonds; and
The minimum denominations in which the college savings bonds may be marketed.
